r-revealed |title=Rabbids Invasion: Debut Date Announced and Trailer Revealed |publisher=IGN |date=July 12, 2013 |accessdate=July 17, 2013}}</ref> On December 17, 2013, Nickelodeon renewed the show for a second season of 26 half-hour blocks, with three segments per block.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tvbythenumbers.zap2it.com/2013/12/17/rabbids-invasion-renewed-by-nickelodeon-for-second-season/223206/ |title=\u2018Rabbids Invasion\u2019 Renewed by Nickelodeon for Second Season |publisher=TVbytheNumbers |date=December 17, 2013 |accessdate=June 19, 2015}}</ref> On June 16, 2015, Nickelodeon renewed the show for a third season.<ref>{{cite web |author=Elsa Keslassy |url=https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/french-toon-studio-teamto-blossoms-at-10-sells-yellowbird-to-universal-1201520552/ |title=French Toon Studio TeamTO Sells \u2018YellowBird\u2019 to Universal |publisher=Variety |date= |accessdate=June 19, 2015}}</ref> A fourth season was announced in July 2018, but that season was not aired internationally on Nick, but instead France 3 and Netflix. <ref>{{Citation |last=Les Lapins Cr\u00e9tins Invasion |title=Les Lapins Cr\u00e9tins \u2013 Teaser Saison 4 |date=July 10, 2018 |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2NF-8yuFeoI|access-date=October 17, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe series has aired on [[Nickelodeon]] in the United States, on [[YTV (TV channel)|YTV]] and [[Nickelodeon (Canada)|Nickelodeon]] in Canada, and on [[France 3]], [[France 4]] and [[Nickelodeon (France)|Nickelodeon]] in France. It premiered on February 3, 2014, in the [[United Kingdom]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.digitalspy.com/gaming/news/a543957/rabbids-invasion-coming-to-uk-on-nicktoons-in-february.html |title=Rabbids Invasion coming to UK in February |last=Martin |first=Liam |work=digitalspy.com |date=January 14, 2014 |accessdate=February 15, 2014}}</ref> and [[Ireland]] and on January 28, 2014, in [[Australia]] and [[New Zealand]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvtonight.com.au/2013/12/foxt